SIMPLE: galloon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Galloon
<hw>Gal*loon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From F. or Sp.
<ets>galon</ets>. See <er>Gala</er>. ]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A narrow
tapelike fabric used for binding hats, shoes, etc., -- sometimes made
ornamental.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A similar bordering or binding of rich material,
such as gold lace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Silver and gold <qex>galloons</qex>, with the like glittering
gewgaws.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gallooned</ent>⟦br⟧
